1
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:09,717
(Santa Anna): We will divide
the army into multiple divisions

2
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:13,762
to pursue and destroy what's
left of the rebel army.

3
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:16,557
I have vital news. Go.

4
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:18,684
(Whooping)

5
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:21,228
(Girl screams)

6
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:22,563
What happened, boy?

7
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,064
Comanche.

8
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:26,108
Comanches.

9
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:30,904
(Horses whinnying)

10
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:32,865
Ahh!

11
00:00:32,907 --> 00:00:35,117
(Santa Anna): This is
not the work of a ghost

12
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,995
This is the work of a man!

13
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,413
Come to relieve me, Tom?

14
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:42,750
Give me one good reason why I shouldn't.

15
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,251
I can't think of one.

16
00:00:47,210 --> 00:00:48,756
No! (Shrieks)

17
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:51,006
You want to kill me?

18
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:54,803
(Houston): Gentlemen, what do you remember?

19
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:56,805
(All): Remember the Alamo!

20
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:03,312
I am waiting.

21
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:04,730
Hyah!

22
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:07,733
(Dramatic music)

23
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:14,965
♪ ♪

24
00:01:15,626 --> 00:01:20,813
== sync & corrections by Wolfen ==
== www.addic7ed.com ==

25
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:30,732
(Militaristic bugles calling)

26
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:32,375
♪ ♪

27
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:43,620
(Indistinct chattering)

28
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:51,712
(Houston): Gentlemen, let's be clear.

29
00:02:52,054 --> 00:02:55,378
I would choose death before betrayal.

30
00:02:55,408 --> 00:02:58,034
But there is no deceit in death.

31
00:02:58,077 --> 00:03:00,453
Betrayal is the willful slaughter of trust.

32
00:03:00,496 --> 00:03:01,997
(Sherman): Sir, we saw the field...

33
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:04,833
Your orders were not to engage.

34
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:08,795
Your insubordination
could have cost us dearly.

35
00:03:08,838 --> 00:03:10,297
As of this moment,

36
00:03:10,339 --> 00:03:12,674
you are now reassigned to second infantry.

37
00:03:12,717 --> 00:03:15,427
- Sir...
- Now, get out of my sight.

38
00:03:20,658 --> 00:03:23,608
Cavalry now belongs to Lamar.

39
00:03:23,638 --> 00:03:25,245
Any objections?

40
00:03:25,287 --> 00:03:27,580
We've bloodied them, Sam.

41
00:03:27,623 --> 00:03:30,834
Perhaps we could regroup
for a counterattack.

42
00:03:30,876 --> 00:03:32,799
General, they're on the defensive.

43
00:03:32,829 --> 00:03:35,372
(Houston): I require
trust from my officers.

44
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,792
(Houston): Towards the Sisters here.

45
00:03:38,835 --> 00:03:41,461
Take out the main barricade
and several points beyond.

46
00:03:41,504 --> 00:03:44,005
Line of infantry 1,000 yards wide.

47
00:03:44,048 --> 00:03:46,466
First Regiment here.

48
00:03:46,509 --> 00:03:49,010
Baker's rifles here.

49
00:03:49,053 --> 00:03:50,512
Sherman's regiment on the flank.

50
00:03:50,555 --> 00:03:52,889
(Baker): Well, I vote we receive an attack.

51
00:03:52,932 --> 00:03:54,558
(Houston): It's not up for a vote, Mosley.

52
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,309
Besides,

53
00:03:56,352 --> 00:03:58,145
that's exactly what Santa
Anna thinks we'll do.

54
00:03:58,187 --> 00:03:59,813
Now, you might reconsider.

55
00:03:59,856 --> 00:04:01,648
We ought not to leave
the security of the woods.

56
00:04:01,691 --> 00:04:03,233
(Hockley): Where are the war dogs now?

57
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:04,568
(Houston): Colonel Lamar,

58
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:06,361
I want your cavalry on the right.

59
00:04:06,404 --> 00:04:09,823
Colonel Seguin and his
Tejanos will man the rearguard.

60
00:04:09,866 --> 00:04:11,158
(Seguin): No. Unacceptable.

61
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,784
Understand, Juan, the courage

62
00:04:12,827 --> 00:04:15,203
of you and your men is
not in question here.

63
00:04:15,246 --> 00:04:18,579
There is such a deep-rooted
hatred towards Mexicans

64
00:04:18,609 --> 00:04:20,167
that I fear your men may have to duck

65
00:04:20,209 --> 00:04:21,751
more than Santanista bullets.

66
00:04:21,794 --> 00:04:24,004
The killing may become indiscriminate.

67
00:04:24,046 --> 00:04:26,256
The blood of our comrades

68
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:29,718
has earned us a place
alongside you, General.

69
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:33,190
My company insists on a frontline attack,

70
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:35,265
come what may.

71
00:04:38,071 --> 00:04:40,520
(Houston): We'll need a way
to distinguish your Tejanos

72
00:04:40,563 --> 00:04:42,105
from Mexican soldiers.

73
00:04:42,688 --> 00:04:43,940
We'll wear...

74
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:45,233
goose feathers

75
00:04:45,276 --> 00:04:46,693
as long as we can sink our teeth

76
00:04:46,736 --> 00:04:49,196
into Santa Anna's neck.

77
00:04:49,238 --> 00:04:51,448
I may have something else.

78
00:04:57,592 --> 00:04:59,498
Let's use these instead.

79
00:05:05,546 --> 00:05:10,634
(Birds chirping)

80
00:05:10,676 --> 00:05:12,269
(Coughs)

81
00:05:12,473 --> 00:05:16,422
_

82
00:05:20,102 --> 00:05:21,269
(Karnes): Goll dang.

83
00:05:21,312 --> 00:05:23,438
General Cos.

84
00:05:23,481 --> 00:05:24,981
Deaf. Deaf!

85
00:05:25,024 --> 00:05:26,650
Mexican reinforcements.

86
00:05:28,277 --> 00:05:29,736
Best tell Houston.

87
00:05:29,779 --> 00:05:32,781
(Soldiers chattering indistinctly)

88
00:05:37,568 --> 00:05:39,436
(Smith): They must've
been marching all night.

89
00:05:39,466 --> 00:05:40,674
(Karnes): They got to be tuckered.

90
00:05:40,704 --> 00:05:42,030
Best get before they see us.

91
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,414
Yep.

92
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:46,052
- Houston!
- Fuego!

93
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:47,095
(Gunshot)

94
00:05:47,137 --> 00:05:48,840
(Yelps) They see us.

95
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:50,306
Run!

96
00:06:01,485 --> 00:06:03,862
Excuse me, Señor Presidente.

97
00:06:03,904 --> 00:06:05,822
General Cos' troops are all present

98
00:06:05,865 --> 00:06:07,073
and accounted for.

99
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:08,408
But exhausted from a long march.

100
00:06:08,450 --> 00:06:09,673
They've been up all night.

101
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,327
So have I.

102
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:13,246
Your Excellency,

103
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:14,430
we should attack now.

104
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:15,531
No.

105
00:06:15,561 --> 00:06:17,750
Houston wants us to attack

106
00:06:17,793 --> 00:06:19,555
so he can cut us down

107
00:06:19,585 --> 00:06:21,588
from the cover of those trees.

108
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:23,756
So we'll wait until
Filisola and Urrea arrive?

109
00:06:23,799 --> 00:06:25,758
Yes, with overwhelming number,

110
00:06:25,801 --> 00:06:27,093
we can surround them.

111
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:28,411
See?

112
00:06:28,441 --> 00:06:31,764
Houston will have nowhere to run.

113
00:06:31,807 --> 00:06:34,267
Feed the men in shifts and let them rest.

114
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,643
Yes, sir.

115
00:06:39,064 --> 00:06:40,982
Houston's skirmish yesterday

116
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:42,817
made no tactical sense.

117
00:06:45,112 --> 00:06:46,446
I don't like it.

118
00:06:48,657 --> 00:06:50,658
(Smith): General, we take that bridge,

119
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:52,201
you won't have to worry about

120
00:06:52,244 --> 00:06:55,330
Santa Anna's reinforcements no more.

121
00:06:55,372 --> 00:06:58,124
You'll be all by your lonesome.

122
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,667
You know I can't afford

123
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,461
to spare you even one extra man.

124
00:07:03,505 --> 00:07:05,089
Forgive me, but destroying that bridge

125
00:07:05,132 --> 00:07:06,799
will cut off our retreat as well.

126
00:07:06,842 --> 00:07:08,176
(Baker): That's a good point.

127
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:14,974
Then we'd better not lose.

128
00:07:25,421 --> 00:07:27,654
Position a crack squadron of dragoons

129
00:07:27,696 --> 00:07:31,115
to protect Vince's Bridge at all costs.

130
00:07:31,158 --> 00:07:32,649
It's our lifeline.

131
00:07:32,679 --> 00:07:35,244
(Almonte): Would it not be
better to abandon this position

132
00:07:35,287 --> 00:07:37,121
until we can rejoin all our armies

133
00:07:37,164 --> 00:07:38,790
and then pursue Houston on the offensive?

134
00:07:38,832 --> 00:07:40,020
Why?

135
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:41,634
We have him!

136
00:07:41,677 --> 00:07:43,803
Here and now.

137
00:07:43,846 --> 00:07:47,682
Let his men sweat it out
while our soldiers rest.

138
00:07:49,018 --> 00:07:50,310
(Almonte): Yes, sir.

139
00:08:06,869 --> 00:08:09,913
What can I do to comfort you, Antonio?

140
00:08:24,572 --> 00:08:27,347
Knowles, get your slack ass up.

141
00:08:27,389 --> 00:08:29,349
(Water splashes)
Morning, sweet pea.

142
00:08:30,768 --> 00:08:31,935
Princess is up.

143
00:08:31,977 --> 00:08:33,394
- Lazy old bitty.
- Come on, now.

144
00:08:33,437 --> 00:08:34,854
Saddled up your horse for you.

145
00:08:34,897 --> 00:08:36,523
(Beans): Come on out. There she is.

146
00:08:36,565 --> 00:08:38,399
- Come on, sweet pea.
- Aww, looking pretty.

147
00:08:38,442 --> 00:08:39,859
(Gator): Hey, girl.

148
00:08:39,902 --> 00:08:41,861
(Smith): All right. That's enough.

149
00:08:41,904 --> 00:08:43,363
It's time.

150
00:08:43,405 --> 00:08:45,740
Knowles, mount up.

151
00:08:47,868 --> 00:08:50,119
I don't know what's ailing you, son,

152
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:51,621
but whatever it is,

153
00:08:51,664 --> 00:08:54,290
you leave it here at camp.

154
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,583
Kick up!

155
00:09:37,559 --> 00:09:39,051
(Martial bugle music)

156
00:09:39,081 --> 00:09:41,004
(Hockley): The general
is not to be disturbed.

157
00:09:41,046 --> 00:09:42,553
Come no further.

158
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:43,764
(Baker): What's he doing? Sleeping?

159
00:09:43,807 --> 00:09:45,516
(Hockley): Step away. Step away.

160
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:46,893
(Sherman): He's awake for 56 days straight;

161
00:09:46,935 --> 00:09:48,519
Now he sleeps?

162
00:09:48,562 --> 00:09:50,146
(Lamar): If he truly wanted to attack,

163
00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:51,564
it should've been at first light.

164
00:09:51,607 --> 00:09:52,899
The weather has been fickle.

165
00:09:52,941 --> 00:09:55,067
It's in our favor now.

166
00:09:55,110 --> 00:09:58,779
(Horses galloping)

167
00:09:58,822 --> 00:10:00,573
Who the hell is this?

168
00:10:00,616 --> 00:10:01,949
(Rusk): Lorca.

169
00:10:01,992 --> 00:10:04,660
(Horse neighs distantly)

170
00:10:05,913 --> 00:10:07,622
Where's General Houston?

171
00:10:07,664 --> 00:10:09,040
(Lamar): State your business.

172
00:10:09,082 --> 00:10:10,875
Saith Jehovah, "Raise your sword

173
00:10:10,918 --> 00:10:12,960
"with abandon and outrage

174
00:10:13,003 --> 00:10:15,046
till the rivers run
red with heathen blood."

175
00:10:16,248 --> 00:10:17,798
Amen.

176
00:10:19,301 --> 00:10:21,093
If you've come to bear arms with us,

177
00:10:21,136 --> 00:10:23,346
then I'll assign you to
Colonel Lamar's cavalry.

178
00:10:23,388 --> 00:10:24,764
I'll be assigned no man.

179
00:10:24,806 --> 00:10:26,307
Be clear on that.

180
00:10:28,018 --> 00:10:31,229
But we'll kill Mexicans alongside you

181
00:10:31,271 --> 00:10:34,920
till every brown breathing
bastard lies dead.

182
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:37,109
Fair enough.

183
00:10:37,152 --> 00:10:39,445
When I'm ready to attack,
I'll give you a sign.

184
00:10:39,488 --> 00:10:40,947
Watch for it.

185
00:10:42,491 --> 00:10:45,159
"Vengeance is mine," saith the Lord.

186
00:10:49,706 --> 00:10:52,250
Sam, you can't trust that loco.

187
00:10:52,292 --> 00:10:56,066
This day, I'd ally with the devil himself.

188
00:10:56,096 --> 00:10:59,006
I think you just did.

189
00:11:18,142 --> 00:11:20,486
(Horse nickers)

190
00:11:21,743 --> 00:11:23,164
Oh.

191
00:11:25,668 --> 00:11:28,202
(Knowles humming)

192
00:11:28,232 --> 00:11:29,910
(Yelps)

193
00:11:30,781 --> 00:11:32,411
Tsk.

194
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:33,650
(Quietly): Mind the horses.

195
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,068
All right. All right. All right.

196
00:11:50,467 --> 00:11:52,010
- Knowles, damn it.
- Listen ti me.

197
00:11:52,052 --> 00:11:53,261
Ain't you supposed to be with the horses?

198
00:11:53,303 --> 00:11:54,595
I know. Just listen.

199
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:56,514
I was wondering, if we blow up the bridge,

200
00:11:56,557 --> 00:11:59,350
how are we supposed to get back across it?

201
00:12:01,437 --> 00:12:02,812
We don't.

202
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:08,735
(Water sloshing)

203
00:12:14,274 --> 00:12:15,687
You hear that?

204
00:12:15,717 --> 00:12:17,009
Something's in the marsh.

205
00:12:17,052 --> 00:12:17,884
(Water sloshing)

206
00:12:17,914 --> 00:12:20,576
(Man): Halt! Hands in the air!

207
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:22,618
Stop right there, or I'll shoot!

208
00:12:22,648 --> 00:12:24,310
- (Gunshots)
- Identify yourself!

209
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:25,668
- We said stop!
- It's me!

210
00:12:25,711 --> 00:12:27,799
It's me, Manuel Flores.

211
00:12:27,829 --> 00:12:30,044
Cease fire! He's one of us.

212
00:12:30,074 --> 00:12:31,791
Manuel, what news?

213
00:12:35,245 --> 00:12:37,497
Santa Anna's army is resting.

214
00:12:37,539 --> 00:12:38,998
His forces are tired.

215
00:12:39,402 --> 00:12:42,271
Emily West says it's time to attack.

216
00:12:42,301 --> 00:12:43,836
More reinforcements are coming.

217
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:45,505
And Miss West herself?

218
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:51,010
She said, "Tell General Houston

219
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,587
"it was right to wait,

220
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:54,297
but attack now."

221
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,757
Very well.

222
00:12:55,799 --> 00:12:57,050
Sir.

223
00:12:59,310 --> 00:13:01,158
(Martial bugle music)

224
00:13:01,188 --> 00:13:02,788
_

225
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,061
(Gator whispers): Easy.

226
00:13:27,873 --> 00:13:30,845
- (Both grunt)
- (Loud thud)

227
00:13:33,892 --> 00:13:37,131
(Martial bugle music)

228
00:13:37,174 --> 00:13:40,718
♪ ♪

229
00:13:41,061 --> 00:13:44,605
(Houston): You were born
to live as free men.

230
00:13:44,648 --> 00:13:47,233
One man took that freedom from you.

231
00:13:47,276 --> 00:13:52,108
One man sent your sons and
brothers to unmarked graves,

232
00:13:52,138 --> 00:13:56,492
your women and children
left homeless and afraid,

233
00:13:56,535 --> 00:13:58,962
burnt your farmlands,

234
00:13:58,992 --> 00:14:01,381
reduced your cherished
homesteads to ashes...

235
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:03,115
one man, a tyrant,

236
00:14:03,145 --> 00:14:05,051
Santa Anna.

237
00:14:07,549 --> 00:14:09,556
Today...

238
00:14:09,843 --> 00:14:12,250
today we avenge our dead.

239
00:14:12,292 --> 00:14:14,961
We honor our loved ones.

240
00:14:15,490 --> 00:14:17,672
Today we are one.

241
00:14:17,714 --> 00:14:21,914
We are all sons of Texas.

242
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:23,611
We give Texas our allegiance.

243
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,563
We give Texas our lives.

244
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:29,742
In the name of Texas,

245
00:14:30,106 --> 00:14:33,580
ready your weapons and
unsheathe your swords,

246
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:35,790
and follow me to victory!

247
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:38,835
(All cheer)

248
00:14:44,401 --> 00:14:45,825
They're retreating.

249
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:47,535
So it seems.

250
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:50,667
(Portilla): The cowards.

251
00:14:53,186 --> 00:14:57,044
(Martial bugle music)

252
00:14:57,087 --> 00:14:59,338
♪ ♪

253
00:14:59,381 --> 00:15:02,833
(Distant shouting in Spanish)

254
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:13,102
(Footsteps)

255
00:15:23,447 --> 00:15:26,407
(Steady drumbeat)

256
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:30,369
♪ ♪

257
00:15:30,412 --> 00:15:31,912
(Whispering): Good. Easy. Good.

258
00:15:31,955 --> 00:15:33,497
Come on. Keep it coming. Keep it coming.

259
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:34,999
(Grunts)

260
00:15:37,313 --> 00:15:39,613
Go on. Go on. We'll string the fuse.

261
00:15:41,157 --> 00:15:44,117
(Martial bugle music)

262
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,760
♪ ♪

263
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:04,012
(Distant bugle music)

264
00:16:04,054 --> 00:16:05,654
♪ ♪

265
00:16:14,523 --> 00:16:15,523
That's the last one.

266
00:16:15,566 --> 00:16:17,275
Go on. I'll fire it up.

267
00:16:17,318 --> 00:16:19,694
Let's see. Let's see. Let's see.

268
00:16:19,737 --> 00:16:22,697
(Martial bugle music)

269
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:24,340
♪ ♪

270
00:16:29,413 --> 00:16:30,872
(West screams, glass shatters)

271
00:16:31,215 --> 00:16:33,215
(West gasping)

272
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:54,709
(Houston): Tell 'em to play that
song, <i>Come To The Bower.</i>

273
00:16:54,739 --> 00:16:57,323
Let me hear it.

274
