335
00:21:53,194 --> 00:21:56,196
You killed my brother at the Alamo.

336
00:21:57,741 --> 00:22:01,535
- (Sobs)
- You killed Jupiter!

337
00:22:01,578 --> 00:22:03,120
(Gunshot, West screams)

338
00:22:03,163 --> 00:22:04,288
(Horse neighs)

339
00:22:04,331 --> 00:22:06,290
(Sobs)

340
00:22:10,670 --> 00:22:12,463
Hold the line!

341
00:22:15,050 --> 00:22:17,009
Attention!

342
00:22:17,052 --> 00:22:18,344
Attention!

343
00:22:19,721 --> 00:22:21,513
Hold ranks!

344
00:22:21,556 --> 00:22:22,848
(Yells)

345
00:22:22,891 --> 00:22:25,476
(Almonte): Form a line here!

346
00:22:25,518 --> 00:22:27,102
And fire at will!

347
00:22:29,397 --> 00:22:30,689
Follow me!

348
00:22:30,732 --> 00:22:32,191
(Soldier): Follow!

349
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:35,235
(Soldiers cheering)

350
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:53,179
No retreat! No retreat!

351
00:22:53,209 --> 00:22:55,381
Stand and fight!

352
00:22:55,423 --> 00:22:57,430
Go now! Go back!

353
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,007
Go back!

354
00:22:59,382 --> 00:23:01,158
Go back!

355
00:23:01,188 --> 00:23:02,563
Back!

356
00:23:02,606 --> 00:23:04,356
(Horse neighs)

357
00:23:04,399 --> 00:23:06,025
Go!

358
00:23:10,071 --> 00:23:13,240
(Water splashing)

359
00:23:13,283 --> 00:23:15,117
(Man screams, grunts)

360
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:18,162
(Water splashing)

361
00:23:27,297 --> 00:23:29,507
(Screaming)

362
00:23:29,549 --> 00:23:32,706
(Coughs, gasping)

363
00:23:32,736 --> 00:23:35,530
(Soldiers screaming)

364
00:23:35,572 --> 00:23:37,878
- No, no, no, no, no...
- (Grunts)

365
00:23:37,908 --> 00:23:38,908
(Soldier): Whoo-hoo!

366
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:40,498
Whoo!

367
00:23:41,075 --> 00:23:43,011
Ride up, boys!

368
00:23:43,041 --> 00:23:45,021
Spread out!

369
00:23:45,051 --> 00:23:47,166
Whoo!

370
00:23:47,209 --> 00:23:50,169
(Soldiers grunting, screaming)

371
00:23:59,454 --> 00:24:01,580
(Gunshot)

372
00:24:01,623 --> 00:24:03,972
(Gunshot)

373
00:24:04,002 --> 00:24:05,084
Hiyah!

374
00:24:05,126 --> 00:24:06,655
That's it. I'm out of here.

375
00:24:06,685 --> 00:24:08,087
Kit!

376
00:24:08,129 --> 00:24:09,588
(Groaning)

377
00:24:09,631 --> 00:24:11,298
Come on.

378
00:24:14,111 --> 00:24:16,821
(Grunts)

379
00:24:16,863 --> 00:24:18,114
Come on, Kit.

380
00:24:18,156 --> 00:24:19,448
(Kit groans)

381
00:24:19,491 --> 00:24:23,411
Sit down right there, Kit. Get down.

382
00:24:23,453 --> 00:24:25,162
(Groans)

383
00:24:25,205 --> 00:24:27,853
Son of a bitch!

384
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:30,793
Get, damn it!

385
00:24:30,836 --> 00:24:32,391
Take this.

386
00:24:34,656 --> 00:24:36,560
I'm coming back for you.

387
00:24:45,458 --> 00:24:47,793
Hey! Hey, get off him.

388
00:24:47,836 --> 00:24:49,419
Get off.

389
00:24:49,462 --> 00:24:52,464
(Both grunting, smacking)

390
00:25:04,936 --> 00:25:06,520
(Smacks, man groans)

391
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:11,667
(Gunshot)

392
00:25:18,741 --> 00:25:20,117
(Growls)

393
00:25:20,159 --> 00:25:21,493
Come on!

394
00:25:33,715 --> 00:25:35,883
(Gunshot)

395
00:25:42,348 --> 00:25:45,392
(Anderson whooping)

396
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:50,606
Mighty white of you, Flores.

397
00:25:50,648 --> 00:25:53,692
(Screaming)

398
00:25:53,735 --> 00:25:55,611
(Both screaming)

399
00:25:55,653 --> 00:25:56,591
(Screaming)

400
00:25:56,621 --> 00:25:58,580
Fight on, men! Follow me!

401
00:25:58,623 --> 00:25:59,709
(Man grunts)

402
00:25:59,739 --> 00:26:01,505
Hiyah!

403
00:26:03,253 --> 00:26:04,753
(Soldier): Remember Goliad!

404
00:26:04,796 --> 00:26:07,589
(Gasping)

405
00:26:07,632 --> 00:26:10,107
Remember the Alamo!

406
00:26:11,745 --> 00:26:13,329
Arm the cannon!

407
00:26:13,371 --> 00:26:15,255
Move!

408
00:26:15,285 --> 00:26:16,203
That's Houston.

409
00:26:16,233 --> 00:26:17,650
Turn the cannon, quickly!

410
00:26:17,692 --> 00:26:18,984
(Houston): Fight on, men!

411
00:26:19,826 --> 00:26:21,046
Yah!

412
00:26:22,071 --> 00:26:23,238
Fire!

413
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:24,948
(Fuse hisses, cannon booms)

414
00:26:24,991 --> 00:26:26,992
(Explosion)

415
00:26:30,228 --> 00:26:31,480
Yah!

416
00:26:31,523 --> 00:26:34,275
(Grunting)

417
00:26:37,195 --> 00:26:39,363
Houston!

418
00:26:39,775 --> 00:26:42,050
Take my horse!

419
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:44,419
Rally your men.

420
00:26:50,950 --> 00:26:52,960
Yah! Yah!

421
00:26:56,662 --> 00:26:58,306
(Gunshot)

422
00:27:06,799 --> 00:27:08,208
(Gunshot)

423
00:27:09,452 --> 00:27:13,254
(Both grunting and smacking)

424
00:27:23,115 --> 00:27:26,935
(Soldier): Mexicans! Remember the Alamo!

425
00:27:28,414 --> 00:27:31,238
(Grunts)

426
00:27:31,268 --> 00:27:35,639
(Coughing)

427
00:27:36,402 --> 00:27:37,927
Go.

428
00:27:43,617 --> 00:27:45,149
(Man grunting and smacking)

429
00:27:45,179 --> 00:27:47,056
(Screams)

430
00:27:47,414 --> 00:27:49,227
(Gunshot)

431
00:27:53,271 --> 00:27:54,730
(Screams)

432
00:27:54,773 --> 00:27:57,775
(Both grunting)

433
00:28:02,718 --> 00:28:04,406
(Karnes grunts, bones snap)

434
00:28:04,449 --> 00:28:06,033
(Gasps)

435
00:28:06,076 --> 00:28:07,159
Captain Karnes.

436
00:28:07,202 --> 00:28:08,494
Colby.

437
00:28:08,524 --> 00:28:12,414
I'm out of shot.

438
00:28:14,362 --> 00:28:16,091
Stay put.

439
00:28:27,196 --> 00:28:28,989
Surround him!

440
00:28:29,031 --> 00:28:32,196
(Gunfire, swords clanging)

441
00:28:32,226 --> 00:28:33,681
To hell with this.

442
00:28:33,711 --> 00:28:35,379
Come on. Yah!

443
00:28:35,421 --> 00:28:36,860
(Almonte): That's their war secretary!

444
00:28:36,890 --> 00:28:39,006
Surround him!

445
00:28:39,036 --> 00:28:42,724
(Knowles shouting)

446
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:44,963
(Rusk): That boy saved my life.

447
00:28:45,006 --> 00:28:46,845
Damnedest thing I ever seen.

448
00:28:48,455 --> 00:28:49,801
Rusk!

449
00:28:49,844 --> 00:28:51,386
(Soldier): Remember the Alamo!

450
00:28:53,431 --> 00:28:54,640
Hiyah!

451
00:28:54,682 --> 00:28:57,976
(Grunting)

452
00:28:58,019 --> 00:28:59,770
Juan! You're one of us.

453
00:28:59,812 --> 00:29:00,979
I am a Tejano!

454
00:29:01,022 --> 00:29:02,898
(Grunts)

455
00:29:11,014 --> 00:29:13,092
I am a Tejano.

456
00:29:13,134 --> 00:29:16,428
(Bugle sounding)

457
00:29:16,471 --> 00:29:19,431
(All grunting and smacking)

458
00:29:26,648 --> 00:29:29,483
I'll find Finisola!

459
00:29:29,526 --> 00:29:31,235
You head west to Urrea!

460
00:29:46,293 --> 00:29:48,961
(Man screaming)

461
00:29:49,004 --> 00:29:50,212
(Gunshot)

462
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:51,463
(Houston grunts)

463
00:29:51,506 --> 00:29:52,506
(Houston groaning)

464
00:29:52,549 --> 00:29:54,300
(Both grunt, swords clang)

465
00:30:00,098 --> 00:30:03,563
(Lorca): If Jesus Christ himself
came down from heaven today

466
00:30:04,021 --> 00:30:06,178
and ordered me to stop killing heathens,

467
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,679
I would not do it!

468
00:30:07,722 --> 00:30:10,182
I would not do it!

469
00:30:10,512 --> 00:30:11,817
(Rusk): Sam!

470
00:30:11,859 --> 00:30:13,110
Tom!

471
00:30:15,863 --> 00:30:17,795
It's just a scratch.

472
00:30:18,716 --> 00:30:20,410
The enemy's been routed.

473
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:22,127
We have to stop the killing.

474
00:30:22,157 --> 00:30:23,512
Get the men under control.

475
00:30:23,554 --> 00:30:26,723
- Cease fire! Cease fire!
- Cease fire!

476
00:30:26,766 --> 00:30:28,517
Cease fire!

477
00:30:28,559 --> 00:30:31,478
(Martial bugle music)

478
00:30:31,521 --> 00:30:33,121
♪ ♪

479
00:30:42,156 --> 00:30:45,784
(Soldier): Boy, turn around!

480
00:30:45,827 --> 00:30:47,285
(Gunshots)

481
00:30:47,328 --> 00:30:50,747
We don't take any prisoners, soldier.

482
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:53,792
(Soldiers shouting, cheering distantly)

483
00:31:03,364 --> 00:31:06,179
(Soldiers shouting, gunfire)

484
00:31:11,844 --> 00:31:13,478
(Thuds, coughs)

485
00:31:13,521 --> 00:31:15,022
(Soldier): Cease fire!

486
00:31:15,064 --> 00:31:17,190
Cease fire!

487
00:31:17,233 --> 00:31:18,605
(Soldier): Cease fire!

488
00:31:18,635 --> 00:31:21,283
(Smith coughing)

489
00:31:28,893 --> 00:31:32,509
(Gunfire)

490
00:31:32,539 --> 00:31:34,515
- Mind your fire.
- Cease fire!

491
00:31:34,545 --> 00:31:35,786
Cease fire.

492
00:31:35,816 --> 00:31:37,519
They're surrendering.

493
00:31:37,549 --> 00:31:41,634
Cease fire. Cease fire.

494
00:31:44,619 --> 00:31:47,746
(Gunshots)

495
00:31:50,457 --> 00:31:54,933
(Speaking Spanish)

496
00:31:55,516 --> 00:31:57,109
We surrender!

497
00:31:57,139 --> 00:31:58,473
- No surrender.
- Stop this.

498
00:31:58,516 --> 00:32:00,271
- We surrender.
- We surrender.

499
00:32:00,301 --> 00:32:02,294
Remember Goliad? Remember Fannin?

500
00:32:02,324 --> 00:32:04,512
(Gunshot)

501
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:09,065
Anderson, take these prisoners to...

502
00:32:12,766 --> 00:32:16,274
(Gunfire)

503
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:25,063
(Almonte): Your orders
are to take prisoners.

504
00:32:25,093 --> 00:32:28,553
The general's orders are to take prisoners.

505
00:32:28,596 --> 00:32:32,891
(Man): We'll take them
just like the Mexicans did.

506
00:32:32,934 --> 00:32:34,559
- Who is it?
- Give them room!

507
00:32:34,602 --> 00:32:36,144
Coming through!

508
00:32:36,537 --> 00:32:37,895
I thought we won.

509
00:32:37,938 --> 00:32:39,336
(Soldier): Those are prisoners, General.

510
00:32:39,366 --> 00:32:41,708
(Rusk): We did win, Sam.

511
00:32:46,339 --> 00:32:47,464
(Grunts)

512
00:32:47,506 --> 00:32:49,216
(Seguin): General Houston!

513
00:32:49,358 --> 00:32:52,777
General, Texas is ours.

514
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:54,612
(Sherman): An astounding victory, General.

515
00:32:54,855 --> 00:32:56,314
(Houston): What's your report?

516
00:32:56,344 --> 00:32:58,650
Around 700 Mexicans killed.

517
00:32:58,692 --> 00:32:59,583
At least that many prisoners.

518
00:32:59,613 --> 00:33:00,985
700?

519
00:33:01,228 --> 00:33:02,143
What about our men?

520
00:33:02,173 --> 00:33:04,502
Only 9 dead and 33 wounded, sir.

521
00:33:04,532 --> 00:33:05,823
(Rusk): 34...

522
00:33:05,866 --> 00:33:07,405
counting you.

523
00:33:07,435 --> 00:33:09,872
And Deaf is unaccounted for.

524
00:33:09,902 --> 00:33:11,187
(Houston): Deaf?

525
00:33:11,217 --> 00:33:13,565
Well, rally the Rangers.

526
00:33:14,007 --> 00:33:14,999
Find him.

527
00:33:15,029 --> 00:33:16,668
Yes, sir.

528
00:33:16,710 --> 00:33:18,432
(Houston): Has Santa Anna been captured?

529
00:33:18,736 --> 00:33:20,484
We are hunting him, sir.

530
00:33:20,514 --> 00:33:22,814
He must be taken alive. You hear me?

531
00:33:24,426 --> 00:33:26,844
Without him, there's no victory.

532
00:33:26,887 --> 00:33:29,472
We've won nothing.

533
00:33:29,515 --> 00:33:30,890
(Groans)

534
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:43,315
(Lamar): Keep searching, men!

535
00:33:48,576 --> 00:33:50,352
(Man): Down here!

536
00:33:51,843 --> 00:33:53,996
Over here!

537
00:33:55,013 --> 00:33:57,125
This way!

538
00:34:18,897 --> 00:34:21,899
(Water rushing)

539
00:34:24,945 --> 00:34:28,820
(Rustling)

540
00:34:28,850 --> 00:34:30,267
Mexicano!

541
00:34:30,309 --> 00:34:31,977
Mexicano. Mexicano!

542
00:34:32,020 --> 00:34:33,478
Benito?

543
00:34:34,123 --> 00:34:35,396
Benito,

544
00:34:35,439 --> 00:34:38,316
you are one of the keepers
of my champion birds.

545
00:34:38,659 --> 00:34:39,543
Presidente?

546
00:34:39,573 --> 00:34:41,953
- Si.
- Presidente.

547
00:34:41,995 --> 00:34:46,707
My friends are all dead.

548
00:34:50,243 --> 00:34:52,685
We lost.

549
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:56,025
We lost a lot of friends today.

550
00:35:01,907 --> 00:35:03,283
(Man): Put him down over there.

551
00:35:06,996 --> 00:35:08,621
I thought you'd be hanging curtains

552
00:35:08,664 --> 00:35:12,750
and darning your fiancé's socks by now.

553
00:35:12,793 --> 00:35:14,511
I'm not going anywhere yet.

554
00:35:14,541 --> 00:35:16,643
Drink this.

555
00:35:17,631 --> 00:35:18,923
(Man): I need to clean this.

556
00:35:18,966 --> 00:35:20,967
Get me some more water.

557
00:35:21,323 --> 00:35:22,951
Do you love him?

558
00:35:24,079 --> 00:35:25,329
Gavin's a goodhearted man.

559
00:35:25,372 --> 00:35:26,831
He's decent.

560
00:35:26,874 --> 00:35:29,166
Daddy loved him, promised
me to him years ago.

561
00:35:29,209 --> 00:35:32,086
Answer my damn question.

562
00:35:36,758 --> 00:35:38,050
(Groaning)

563
00:35:38,093 --> 00:35:39,677
(Man): Just get him some laudanum.

564
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:42,021
(Panting)

565
00:35:42,051 --> 00:35:46,480
You don't want what I got to give, no way.

566
00:35:46,510 --> 00:35:48,382
The next bullet that comes
my way might be my last.

567
00:35:48,412 --> 00:35:50,242
Don't say such things.

568
00:35:50,272 --> 00:35:51,539
You know, my whole life,

569
00:35:51,582 --> 00:35:54,084
people have been telling
me what's good for me.

570
00:35:54,126 --> 00:35:56,962
(Man): Back over when you've got a minute.

571
00:35:57,753 --> 00:36:00,253
You'd be a damn fool not to go with him.

572
00:36:02,426 --> 00:36:05,178
No, you're the fool, Kit Acklin.

573
00:36:09,745 --> 00:36:12,085
(Crunching, man screaming)

574
00:36:12,115 --> 00:36:14,462
(Houston): Where am I?

575
00:36:14,905 --> 00:36:16,844
Did they cut my leg off?

576
00:36:16,874 --> 00:36:19,417
(Doc Ewing): No, but
your ankle was shattered.

577
00:36:19,459 --> 00:36:20,981
If sepsis sets in,

578
00:36:21,011 --> 00:36:24,305
you will die a slow, miserable death.

579
00:36:24,348 --> 00:36:25,640
Any word from Emily?

580
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:26,606
(Doc Ewing): No.

581
00:36:26,636 --> 00:36:28,976
We got to get you to New Orleans.

582
00:36:29,019 --> 00:36:31,479
If not, should you fall unconscious,

583
00:36:31,522 --> 00:36:33,815
I will have that leg off.

584
00:36:33,857 --> 00:36:37,527
I'll take my chances in New Orleans.

585
00:36:40,039 --> 00:36:41,360
Emily.

586
00:36:41,390 --> 00:36:44,392
(Distant gunfire)

587
00:36:57,740 --> 00:37:00,784
(Coughing)

588
00:37:06,466 --> 00:37:09,334
(Indistinct shouting)

589
00:37:09,377 --> 00:37:11,378
(Shushing)

590
00:37:15,216 --> 00:37:18,510
(Distant shouting)

591
00:37:18,552 --> 00:37:21,596
(Distant cannonfire)

592
00:37:25,393 --> 00:37:28,353
(Whimpering)

593
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:37,320
Am I dying, padre?

594
00:37:42,953 --> 00:37:43,952
Si.

595
00:37:54,215 --> 00:37:56,215
(Sobbing)

596
00:38:03,764 --> 00:38:05,140
(Karnes): Deaf.

597
00:38:06,067 --> 00:38:07,456
Deaf!

598
00:38:07,897 --> 00:38:10,061
(Flames crackling)

599
00:38:12,765 --> 00:38:15,680
(Distant banging)

600
00:38:29,534 --> 00:38:33,042
(Loud banging)

601
00:38:35,461 --> 00:38:37,255
(Knowles): Oh-ho!

602
00:38:38,674 --> 00:38:41,342
Well, chop my legs and call me Shorty.

603
00:38:41,385 --> 00:38:44,095
Vern! Vern, ain't this swank?

604
00:38:44,688 --> 00:38:45,876
Ain't this swank?

605
00:38:45,906 --> 00:38:46,998
Close this thing.

606
00:38:47,028 --> 00:38:48,396
Hey, take a look at this.

607
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:49,592
Take a look at this.

608
00:38:49,635 --> 00:38:51,344
(Breathes noisily): One second.

609
00:38:51,946 --> 00:38:54,153
General Santa Annabella herself.

610
00:38:54,183 --> 00:38:56,199
Ooh, well, hello there.

611
00:38:56,229 --> 00:38:58,447
Hello. Hello, there.

612
00:38:58,477 --> 00:39:00,311
The spoils of war, son.

613
00:39:00,354 --> 00:39:01,842
We grab what we can hold,

614
00:39:01,872 --> 00:39:03,564
and we cut out of here tonight.

615
00:39:03,607 --> 00:39:05,066
Yes, sir. Whoa, whoa, no.

616
00:39:05,108 --> 00:39:06,359
I don't know.

617
00:39:06,401 --> 00:39:07,610
Vern, Vern, hey, Vern.

618
00:39:07,653 --> 00:39:09,491
You got to understand.

619
00:39:09,521 --> 00:39:11,147
I'm a hero now.

620
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:14,288
I saved the war secretary's life.

621
00:39:14,694 --> 00:39:18,529
I heard you tripped
over a bunch of Mexicans.

622
00:39:18,572 --> 00:39:19,530
It...

623
00:39:19,573 --> 00:39:20,508
(Thudding and grunting)

624
00:39:20,538 --> 00:39:21,999
Ha!

625
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,664
Eureka.

626
00:39:30,234 --> 00:39:32,193
Holy shit.

627
00:39:43,914 --> 00:39:45,206
(Gun cocks)

628
00:39:47,209 --> 00:39:48,710
(Colby Pitt): Surrender, Mexican,

629
00:39:48,752 --> 00:39:51,754
or I'll kill you deader than last Tuesday.

630
00:39:51,797 --> 00:39:55,550
On your knees. On your knees.

631
00:39:55,593 --> 00:39:57,927
Are you alone?

632
00:39:58,470 --> 00:39:59,887
Maybe.

633
00:40:05,703 --> 00:40:07,608
Hands up.

634
00:40:07,638 --> 00:40:09,097
Hands up!

635
00:40:18,106 --> 00:40:19,566
God damn. We can't get it all now.

636
00:40:19,608 --> 00:40:22,193
Got to come back before we head out.

637
00:40:22,236 --> 00:40:24,362
- (Metallic clattering)
- (Gasps)

638
00:40:24,755 --> 00:40:27,548
Well, goodness gracious.

639
00:40:27,591 --> 00:40:29,472
What is this?

640
00:40:30,844 --> 00:40:34,472
It's the mother lode...
Santa Anna's treasure.

641
00:40:34,515 --> 00:40:36,474
You snakes weren't gonna tell me about it?

642
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:37,684
Well, why should we?

643
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:39,548
We found it.

644
00:40:39,578 --> 00:40:42,163
Lucky for me,

645
00:40:42,193 --> 00:40:43,848
so did I.

646
00:40:43,891 --> 00:40:47,323
(Karnes): That there must
be El Presidente's tent.

647
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:49,583
(Elwood): Cover this shit up. That's right.

648
00:40:49,613 --> 00:40:51,739
- All right.
- Cover it up.

649
00:40:51,782 --> 00:40:54,855
- All right.
- That's right.

650
00:41:00,290 --> 00:41:02,896
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-whee!

651
00:41:02,926 --> 00:41:05,303
Awful highfalutin.

652
00:41:05,345 --> 00:41:07,555
(Laughs)

653
00:41:07,598 --> 00:41:10,187
Looks like this place done been looted.

654
00:41:10,217 --> 00:41:13,052
We was just picking up
a few souvenirs, man.

655
00:41:13,095 --> 00:41:14,825
Spoils of war and such.

656
00:41:14,855 --> 00:41:17,277
Well, you know that looting

657
00:41:17,307 --> 00:41:21,611
could get you court-martialed and shot.

658
00:41:21,641 --> 00:41:24,897
- (Laughs nervously)
- What, you mean...

659
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:29,861
even for a token or two
for our loyalty to Texas?

660
00:41:29,903 --> 00:41:31,785
Listen up.

661
00:41:31,815 --> 00:41:34,171
All this belongs to the Texas government.

662
00:41:34,441 --> 00:41:36,588
So if you don't mind, I'll take...

663
00:41:36,618 --> 00:41:39,537
- Captain, you all right?
- Son of a bitch.

664
00:41:40,736 --> 00:41:42,707
(Quietly): Damn.

665
00:41:42,750 --> 00:41:46,807
Oh, lookee here.

666
00:41:47,248 --> 00:41:49,303
Would you look at that?

667
00:41:49,333 --> 00:41:52,592
Santa Anna must've buried that, right?

668
00:41:52,634 --> 00:41:54,594
Must have.

669
00:41:54,636 --> 00:41:55,970
All of it.

670
00:42:01,656 --> 00:42:05,980
(Loud thud)

671
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:08,900
(Metallic clinking and thud)

672
00:42:08,942 --> 00:42:10,902
(Quietly): Damn.

673
00:42:10,944 --> 00:42:13,738
(Indistinct chatter)

674
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:16,783
(Scattered cheering)

675
00:42:25,834 --> 00:42:27,877
(Man): Yeah!

676
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,922
(All cheering)

677
00:42:34,343 --> 00:42:35,593
How about that?

678
00:42:35,636 --> 00:42:38,721
(Man): Vive, El Presidente!

679
00:42:38,764 --> 00:42:40,681
(Man): Yeah!

680
00:42:40,724 --> 00:42:43,356
(Doc Ewing): It's a tincture of opium, Sam,

681
00:42:43,386 --> 00:42:46,103
for the pain.

682
00:42:46,146 --> 00:42:49,023
Quart of warm whiskey
would work just as well.

683
00:42:52,453 --> 00:42:55,413
General, you've got to see this.

684
00:42:55,456 --> 00:42:56,619
He needs to rest.

685
00:42:56,649 --> 00:42:58,149
I need fresh air.

686
00:42:58,192 --> 00:43:00,527
Fetch my clothes.

687
00:43:00,569 --> 00:43:03,279
Haul me up, Tom.

688
00:43:03,322 --> 00:43:06,324
(Hockley): By my count,
we have over 20,000 pieces

689
00:43:06,367 --> 00:43:07,825
of silver and gold...

690
00:43:07,868 --> 00:43:10,495
all of Santa Anna's
personal valuables, sir.

691
00:43:10,538 --> 00:43:13,206
(Seguin): General, we must give
these to the people of Tejas.

692
00:43:13,249 --> 00:43:15,500
(Rusk): Gentlemen, there is
no discussion on this matter.

693
00:43:15,543 --> 00:43:17,168
Funds seized from the enemy

694
00:43:17,211 --> 00:43:20,672
belong to the newly liberated Republic.

695
00:43:20,714 --> 00:43:22,173
(Man): Another group going in.

696
00:43:22,216 --> 00:43:24,676
(Rusk): It all goes to Texas.

697
00:43:28,722 --> 00:43:31,849
Karnes, that soldier there.

698
00:43:31,892 --> 00:43:33,101
Bring him to me.

699
00:43:33,143 --> 00:43:34,519
(Karnes): Sir.

700
00:43:34,562 --> 00:43:36,521
Flores, fetch Colonel Almonte.

701
00:43:36,564 --> 00:43:38,898
Yes, sir.

702
00:43:38,928 --> 00:43:40,191
(Man): Move!

703
00:43:40,234 --> 00:43:41,979
(Indistinct chatter)

704
00:43:42,009 --> 00:43:45,109
- (Flores): Colonel Almonte...
- (Karnes): Come on.

705
00:43:58,736 --> 00:44:00,695
So you're a private.

706
00:44:01,285 --> 00:44:04,537
Si, señor.

707
00:44:05,217 --> 00:44:07,598
Colonel Almonte,

708
00:44:07,628 --> 00:44:10,588
why do your men salute him?

709
00:44:10,631 --> 00:44:11,835
Regretfully,

710
00:44:11,865 --> 00:44:13,987
I do not know all my soldiers, sir.

711
00:44:14,017 --> 00:44:15,889
That's too bad.

712
00:44:15,919 --> 00:44:17,169
Private Pitt,

713
00:44:17,897 --> 00:44:20,151
execute your prisoner.

714
00:44:22,418 --> 00:44:23,835
(Colby Pitt): Yes, sir.

715
00:44:25,337 --> 00:44:27,505
(Houston): No, private.

716
00:44:28,673 --> 00:44:30,341
Put him up against a tree

717
00:44:30,384 --> 00:44:32,923
so his brains don't splatter.

718
00:44:36,122 --> 00:44:39,642
I am Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna.

719
00:44:39,685 --> 00:44:40,651
Wait. He's Santa Anna?

720
00:44:40,681 --> 00:44:44,268
And I am Sam Houston.

721
00:44:44,298 --> 00:44:46,466
El Presidente, General,

722
00:44:46,736 --> 00:44:48,757
I cannot express

723
00:44:48,787 --> 00:44:52,555
how glad I am to meet you.

724
00:44:52,871 --> 00:44:54,604
I ask to be treated as a general should be

725
00:44:54,634 --> 00:44:57,168
when made a prisoner of war.

726
00:44:57,211 --> 00:44:58,461
Men!

727
00:44:58,504 --> 00:45:00,547
We captured Santa Anna!

728
00:45:00,929 --> 00:45:03,508
We must convene a tribunal and execute him.

729
00:45:03,551 --> 00:45:06,177
(Baker): Death by firing squad!

730
00:45:06,220 --> 00:45:09,180
(All): yeah!

731
00:45:09,223 --> 00:45:10,515
(All talking at once)

732
00:45:10,558 --> 00:45:12,058
Yeah!

733
00:45:12,101 --> 00:45:15,103
(All shouting)

734
00:45:16,905 --> 00:45:19,991
The conqueror of the Napoleon of the West

735
00:45:20,476 --> 00:45:23,870
can afford to be generous
to the vanquished, no?

736
00:45:23,912 --> 00:45:25,788
You should have remembered that, sir,

737
00:45:25,831 --> 00:45:27,498
at the Alamo.

738
00:45:27,541 --> 00:45:30,376
At the Alamo, your defenders chose to die.

739
00:45:30,419 --> 00:45:32,416
You offered them no alternative.

740
00:45:32,446 --> 00:45:34,568
- (Spits)
- Bastardo.

741
00:45:34,598 --> 00:45:36,307
Juan...

742
00:45:38,151 --> 00:45:39,819
This is war, sir,

743
00:45:39,861 --> 00:45:43,168
and no one here is good or bad,

744
00:45:43,693 --> 00:45:45,863
just winners

745
00:45:45,893 --> 00:45:49,473
and losers.

746
00:45:49,503 --> 00:45:51,898
I acted under the orders
from my government.

747
00:45:51,940 --> 00:45:54,191
You are yourself the government.

748
00:45:54,234 --> 00:45:55,776
That's damn right.

749
00:45:55,819 --> 00:45:58,029
(Rusk): Texas formed a
recognized government.

750
00:45:58,071 --> 00:45:59,697
We are not pirates.

751
00:45:59,740 --> 00:46:01,699
The rules of war applied.

752
00:46:01,742 --> 00:46:04,201
General, why are we even
talking to this murderer?

753
00:46:04,244 --> 00:46:05,849
He needs to swing.

754
00:46:05,879 --> 00:46:08,673
Firing squad, here and now!

755
00:46:08,716 --> 00:46:12,343
(All): Yeah!

756
00:46:12,386 --> 00:46:15,471
(All talking at once): Do it!

757
00:46:15,514 --> 00:46:16,973
- Yeah!
- (Men shouting)

758
00:46:30,994 --> 00:46:34,866
(Men shouting)

759
00:46:34,908 --> 00:46:37,156
(Houston): There'll be no firing squad.

760
00:46:37,186 --> 00:46:39,178
(Man): We want blood!

761
00:46:39,221 --> 00:46:41,868
(Houston): That cannot happen.

762
00:46:41,898 --> 00:46:45,309
Alive, Santa Anna is of great value to us.

763
00:46:45,502 --> 00:46:47,962
If we execute him,

764
00:46:48,005 --> 00:46:51,298
he'll just be another dead soldier.

765
00:46:51,612 --> 00:46:53,155
Let us take our reparations.

766
00:46:53,185 --> 00:46:55,194
Open his war chest.

767
00:46:55,237 --> 00:46:57,154
Gold to every man in my command.

768
00:46:57,197 --> 00:47:01,367
Equal shares for all those
who risked their lives.

769
00:47:01,409 --> 00:47:03,786
General Seguin, General Sherman,

770
00:47:03,829 --> 00:47:05,621
show the men.

771
00:47:05,664 --> 00:47:06,914
Divvy it up.

772
00:47:06,957 --> 00:47:09,834
(Sherman): Yes, sir.

773
00:47:09,876 --> 00:47:12,878
(All cheering)

774
00:47:33,150 --> 00:47:36,530
General, we're taking him.

775
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:37,858
Retribution goes hand in hand

776
00:47:37,888 --> 00:47:39,346
with victory.

777
00:47:39,389 --> 00:47:41,182
Present your prisoner.

778
00:47:41,224 --> 00:47:43,517
I will not.

779
00:47:46,474 --> 00:47:48,355
All right, fine by me.

780
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:52,977
We end it all now.

781
00:47:53,020 --> 00:47:55,980
My only reason for living

782
00:47:56,023 --> 00:47:57,940
is to slay him.

783
00:47:59,347 --> 00:48:01,736
Ride on out of here while you can.

784
00:48:01,778 --> 00:48:04,131
Shut your mouth, boy.

785
00:48:04,161 --> 00:48:05,856
Shoot me first.

786
00:48:06,575 --> 00:48:08,489
You don't think I will?

787
00:48:09,570 --> 00:48:12,599
Soldiers, ready arms!

788
00:48:36,664 --> 00:48:38,289
Don't fool yourself.

789
00:48:38,332 --> 00:48:41,471
Santa Anna will die!

790
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:42,835
It's just a matter

791
00:48:42,878 --> 00:48:46,046
of how many of us he takes with him.

792
00:48:49,843 --> 00:48:52,136
You understand me?

793
00:49:55,617 --> 00:49:58,535
(Coughs)

794
00:50:11,425 --> 00:50:12,591
Charmaine.

795
00:50:12,634 --> 00:50:13,783
(Horse neighs)

796
00:50:13,813 --> 00:50:15,678
(Groans)

797
00:50:15,720 --> 00:50:17,876
Come here, girl.

798
00:50:17,906 --> 00:50:19,223
Come here.

799
00:50:19,266 --> 00:50:21,387
You saved me today.

800
00:50:33,672 --> 00:50:35,563
Oh, sweet girl.

801
00:50:37,724 --> 00:50:39,105
(Groans)

802
00:50:39,135 --> 00:50:42,976
(Horse whinnies)

803
00:50:44,111 --> 00:50:46,141
No.

804
00:50:50,288 --> 00:50:54,458
Why'd you have to go do that for?

805
00:50:54,501 --> 00:50:56,001
Why'd you do that?

806
00:51:18,024 --> 00:51:20,234
I'm so sorry.

807
00:51:22,537 --> 00:51:24,038
(Crying): I'm so sorry.

808
00:51:28,835 --> 00:51:31,337
Come on. Let's get you off that leg.

809
00:51:31,379 --> 00:51:33,547
Let's get you off that leg, okay?

810
00:51:50,236 --> 00:51:52,558
You do me a favor.

811
00:52:00,205 --> 00:52:02,743
You do me a favor.

812
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:05,788
You wait for me. You hear?

813
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:08,754
You wait for me.

814
00:52:08,784 --> 00:52:11,535
You'll be seeing me real soon.

815
00:52:13,622 --> 00:52:14,872
(Gun cocks)

816
00:52:14,915 --> 00:52:17,541
(Exhales)

817
00:52:17,584 --> 00:52:18,959
(Gunshot)

818
00:52:19,002 --> 00:52:20,669
(Gunshot echoing)

819
00:52:20,712 --> 00:52:23,380
(Crying)

820
00:52:35,268 --> 00:52:36,602
(Snickers)

821
00:52:36,645 --> 00:52:39,647
(Indistinct chatter in Spanish)

822
00:52:54,788 --> 00:52:57,039
(Distant galloping)

823
00:52:57,082 --> 00:52:58,290
(Man screaming)

824
00:52:58,333 --> 00:53:02,044
(All speaking Spanish)

825
00:53:02,087 --> 00:53:03,254
(Lorca): Get every one of them!

826
00:53:03,296 --> 00:53:04,588
Every one of them!

827
00:53:04,631 --> 00:53:05,798
Hey, come on!

828
00:53:05,841 --> 00:53:07,133
(Gunshot, woman screams)

829
00:53:07,175 --> 00:53:08,467
Come on!

830
00:53:08,510 --> 00:53:11,053
(People shouting indistinctly)

831
00:53:14,057 --> 00:53:15,516
(Panting)

832
00:53:15,559 --> 00:53:20,271
(Gunshot)

833
00:53:20,313 --> 00:53:23,315
(Laughter)

834
00:53:25,068 --> 00:53:26,402
(Gasps)

835
00:53:29,863 --> 00:53:31,365
No! He's just a child.

836
00:53:31,408 --> 00:53:32,783
Nits make lice.

837
00:53:32,826 --> 00:53:35,202
We're done killing women and children!

838
00:53:35,245 --> 00:53:36,787
Then get out of here!

839
00:53:36,830 --> 00:53:38,964
I aim to kill Mexicans,
and I ain't done yet.

840
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:41,292
- Go.
- All right.

841
00:53:41,334 --> 00:53:43,168
Just go, man. Go.

842
00:53:43,710 --> 00:53:45,254
Go!

843
00:53:45,297 --> 00:53:46,839
Come on, man.

844
00:53:50,886 --> 00:53:54,138
Give me the boy.

845
00:54:00,854 --> 00:54:02,980
(Gunshot)

846
00:54:09,196 --> 00:54:10,584
(Thunder rumbles)

847
00:54:10,614 --> 00:54:12,073
(Houston): Any word from Deaf?

848
00:54:12,115 --> 00:54:13,449
(Flores): No, General.

849
00:54:13,892 --> 00:54:15,100
And Miss West?

850
00:54:15,143 --> 00:54:16,727
Nothing, sir.

851
00:54:19,335 --> 00:54:21,268
Very well.

852
00:54:26,279 --> 00:54:29,281
You wanted to keep me alive, no?

853
00:54:29,324 --> 00:54:32,409
Once you are gone, these men will hang me.

854
00:54:34,871 --> 00:54:36,121
Tell me something.

855
00:54:36,164 --> 00:54:39,306
Your generals... will they retreat

856
00:54:39,336 --> 00:54:42,177
once they're informed
you've been taken hostage?

857
00:54:42,220 --> 00:54:43,216
No.

858
00:54:43,696 --> 00:54:45,781
Their orders are to engage.

859
00:54:50,711 --> 00:54:53,755
Then I recommend you rescind those orders.

860
00:54:55,442 --> 00:54:58,610
So you want Texas

861
00:54:58,653 --> 00:55:01,572
in exchange for my life, huh?

862
00:55:01,614 --> 00:55:03,073
Sounds like a trade.

863
00:55:03,116 --> 00:55:04,283
(Rusk): Only President Burnett

864
00:55:04,325 --> 00:55:06,368
can negotiate a treaty.

865
00:55:06,411 --> 00:55:08,245
(Houston): Well, he
can't very well negotiate

866
00:55:08,288 --> 00:55:10,080
if El Presidente here is dead.

867
00:55:10,123 --> 00:55:11,582
Now, can he?

868
00:55:16,463 --> 00:55:18,088
(Woman): I'll need them vials.

869
00:55:18,131 --> 00:55:21,091
(Indistinct chatter)

870
00:55:25,130 --> 00:55:26,618
Kit,

871
00:55:26,648 --> 00:55:28,751
are you sure you're fit to ride?

872
00:55:28,781 --> 00:55:30,943
Hey, now, don't fuss.

873
00:55:30,985 --> 00:55:32,319
In case I need tending to,

874
00:55:32,362 --> 00:55:35,557
Doc Ewing's coming with the General.

875
00:55:36,574 --> 00:55:38,367
I'll see you when I get back.

876
00:55:38,409 --> 00:55:39,910
I certainly hope so...

877
00:55:39,953 --> 00:55:42,788
if you don't get yourself killed.

878
00:56:15,738 --> 00:56:19,871
(Elwood whistling)

879
00:56:26,499 --> 00:56:29,501
(Doc Ewing): Sarah, you got
my medical bag packed up yet?

880
00:56:32,088 --> 00:56:34,828
I'll be seeing you.

881
00:56:35,108 --> 00:56:37,234
(Doc Ewing): Sarah!

882
00:56:46,327 --> 00:56:48,203
Where you heading to, Vern?

883
00:56:50,628 --> 00:56:53,083
War is over for me, Knowles.

884
00:56:53,126 --> 00:56:54,293
I done my duty.

885
00:56:54,335 --> 00:56:56,587
Had my fill of taking orders.

886
00:56:56,855 --> 00:56:59,047
Might head on down to Victoria.

887
00:56:59,090 --> 00:57:00,879
Mm.

888
00:57:00,909 --> 00:57:02,493
You want to know my guess?

889
00:57:02,966 --> 00:57:06,413
You and Gator are going after that bank.

890
00:57:06,456 --> 00:57:09,500
Gator's so full of bunkum,
if he told me water was wet,

891
00:57:09,542 --> 00:57:12,503
I'd have to poke my finger
in and feel for myself.

892
00:57:13,947 --> 00:57:15,781
Kit didn't trust him.

893
00:57:16,123 --> 00:57:17,245
You ought not to neither.

894
00:57:17,275 --> 00:57:18,921
Well, I ain't robbing no bank.

895
00:57:18,951 --> 00:57:20,457
I'm a hero now.

896
00:57:20,487 --> 00:57:23,155
Got a reputation to uphold.

897
00:57:27,959 --> 00:57:31,705
Well, if you want to ride
your hero ass along with me,

898
00:57:31,748 --> 00:57:33,123
you're welcome.

899
00:57:34,709 --> 00:57:36,788
Well...

900
00:57:38,505 --> 00:57:40,631
no, thank you, my friend.

901
00:57:41,381 --> 00:57:44,259
I reckon I'll just stay put.

902
00:57:47,610 --> 00:57:49,797
Good luck with that shit.

903
00:57:52,905 --> 00:57:55,124
Tell them boys I say adios.

904
00:57:55,154 --> 00:57:57,071
All right.

905
00:58:02,081 --> 00:58:04,429
You lily-livered weasel.

906
00:58:04,472 --> 00:58:05,722
How in the hell am I supposed

907
00:58:05,765 --> 00:58:07,504
to take this bank by myself?

908
00:58:07,534 --> 00:58:11,036
Well, why don't you
recruit Karnes and Anderson?

909
00:58:23,032 --> 00:58:26,723
(Houston): Tom, I want you
to ride on ahead to Burnett.

910
00:58:26,753 --> 00:58:29,546
Formalize our agreement with Santa Anna.

911
00:58:29,589 --> 00:58:32,153
Buckley and Seguin will
take charge of the army

912
00:58:32,183 --> 00:58:33,340
while I'm away.

913
00:58:33,370 --> 00:58:35,268
(Rusk): You get that leg healed up, Sam.

914
00:58:35,311 --> 00:58:36,561
Texas needs you.

915
00:58:36,591 --> 00:58:37,562
(Grunts)

916
00:58:37,592 --> 00:58:41,444
You just gonna leave me behind, is that it?

917
00:58:41,501 --> 00:58:44,770
Well, I'll be damned.

918
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:46,438
I'd about given up on you.

919
00:58:47,805 --> 00:58:50,534
I had to lay Charmaine to rest.

920
00:58:52,574 --> 00:58:54,113
(Karnes): Partner, damn.

921
00:58:54,155 --> 00:58:56,073
You look like something the cat dragged in

922
00:58:56,116 --> 00:58:58,594
that the goat wouldn't eat.

923
00:58:58,624 --> 00:58:59,878
Right here.

924
00:58:59,908 --> 00:59:00,744
(Coughs)

925
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:03,080
Let it out.

926
00:59:03,351 --> 00:59:05,207
Let it on out.

927
00:59:08,161 --> 00:59:09,551
(Houston): Private Pitt.

928
00:59:10,984 --> 00:59:12,214
The man that captured Santa Anna

929
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:14,680
ought to make a damn good Ranger.

930
00:59:14,710 --> 00:59:16,456
Your first assignment:

931
00:59:16,486 --> 00:59:18,762
Take Captain Smith home to his wife.

932
00:59:18,805 --> 00:59:20,417
Yes, sir.

933
00:59:20,447 --> 00:59:23,309
Sorry to hear about Charmaine.

934
00:59:23,351 --> 00:59:26,787
(Smith): Anybody fetch me a new mount yet?

935
00:59:26,817 --> 00:59:28,824
(Doc Ewing): Get a wagon
and lay him down in back.

936
00:59:28,993 --> 00:59:31,066
You're in no condition to go, Deaf.

937
00:59:35,525 --> 00:59:37,948
What'd you say, Sam?

938
00:59:38,209 --> 00:59:40,463
You need to look me in the eye.

939
00:59:44,331 --> 00:59:48,042
I said you're not going.

940
00:59:48,084 --> 00:59:50,919
And who's gonna look after
your old crippled ass?

941
00:59:52,783 --> 00:59:55,495
Karnes will take command of the Rangers.

942
00:59:56,843 --> 00:59:58,469
Just gonna throw me away.

943
00:59:58,511 --> 01:00:00,165
Is that it?

944
01:00:03,731 --> 01:00:06,310
Go home, old friend.

945
01:00:08,005 --> 01:00:11,361
The Republic of Texas
is grateful for your service.

946
01:00:11,391 --> 01:00:12,911
Go on.

947
01:00:12,941 --> 01:00:14,017
(Doc Ewing): All right.

948
01:00:14,060 --> 01:00:17,354
Colby, get him in the medical tent.

949
01:00:17,702 --> 01:00:19,398
Got to get Houston to New Orleans

950
01:00:19,440 --> 01:00:23,068
and Santa Anna to his peace talks.

951
01:00:23,111 --> 01:00:24,736
You take care of yourself, Deaf.

952
01:00:25,813 --> 01:00:27,489
(Houston): Let's move out.

953
01:00:27,532 --> 01:00:29,491
(Smith): Sam.

954
01:00:29,534 --> 01:00:30,867
Sam.

955
01:00:30,910 --> 01:00:33,453
I'll tell you when I'm done.

956
01:00:38,384 --> 01:00:39,801
Yah.

957
01:01:04,778 --> 01:01:06,995
(Groaning)

958
01:01:10,781 --> 01:01:13,544
(Fly buzzing)

959
01:01:34,690 --> 01:01:37,317
(Doc Ewing): You just had one, Sam.

960
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:38,526
That's quite enough.

961
01:01:38,569 --> 01:01:39,861
Mmm!

962
01:01:47,720 --> 01:01:50,221
You think you are a man of destiny,

963
01:01:50,264 --> 01:01:52,140
but all I see

964
01:01:52,183 --> 01:01:54,184
is President Jackson's puppet.

965
01:01:56,228 --> 01:01:58,938
All I see is a man in a chicken coop.

966
01:01:59,081 --> 01:02:01,708
I am defending my people
against pirates like you,

967
01:02:01,750 --> 01:02:04,081
stealing our land.

968
01:02:04,111 --> 01:02:07,906
History will sweep you
aside with a footnote.

969
01:02:07,948 --> 01:02:09,491
Perhaps.

970
01:02:09,533 --> 01:02:10,867
Better a footnote

971
01:02:10,910 --> 01:02:13,453
than a whole book of abominations.

972
01:02:13,496 --> 01:02:15,121
(Chuckles)

973
01:02:15,164 --> 01:02:18,291
No difference with what
you did in San Jacinto.

974
01:02:18,334 --> 01:02:20,335
We are men on opposite sides,

975
01:02:20,377 --> 01:02:22,796
yet there is much we share.

976
01:02:22,838 --> 01:02:25,340
A love of our countries,

977
01:02:25,382 --> 01:02:29,010
a love of... other things.

978
01:02:29,053 --> 01:02:31,429
A remarkable woman, Miss West.

979
01:02:32,608 --> 01:02:34,766
An extraordinary woman,

980
01:02:34,809 --> 01:02:37,056
especially in bed

981
01:02:37,086 --> 01:02:39,129
when she's screaming with pleasure.

982
01:02:41,132 --> 01:02:42,632
I hear women are quite skilled

983
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:45,051
at pretending that sort of thing.

984
01:02:45,094 --> 01:02:48,805
"Oh, Antonio, yes, yes, more.

985
01:02:48,848 --> 01:02:50,473
Give me more."

986
01:02:50,516 --> 01:02:53,184
Give him another one, Doc.

987
01:02:53,227 --> 01:02:56,271
He's wrestling with
what defeat tastes like.

988
01:03:11,446 --> 01:03:14,831
(Water splashing)

989
01:03:23,632 --> 01:03:26,468
Colonel Portilla's got Emily West.

990
01:03:26,510 --> 01:03:28,219
Wants to trade her for Santa Anna.

991
01:03:30,401 --> 01:03:32,223
A whore for a chief of state.

992
01:03:33,610 --> 01:03:36,269
Portilla is losing his mind.

993
01:03:42,810 --> 01:03:44,602
Give this back to him.

994
01:03:46,366 --> 01:03:47,891
Flores.

995
01:03:49,758 --> 01:03:51,050
Sir?

996
01:03:51,093 --> 01:03:54,053
(Speaking foreign language)

997
01:03:54,096 --> 01:03:55,388
Yes, sir.

998
01:03:55,431 --> 01:03:56,723
Anderson!

999
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,078
- Yeah.
- Get ready.

1000
01:04:19,121 --> 01:04:20,079
God is with us.

1001
01:04:20,122 --> 01:04:21,310
Ha!

1002
01:04:21,340 --> 01:04:22,716
Beads and whiskey

1003
01:04:22,758 --> 01:04:24,342
always worked for me before.

1004
01:04:28,931 --> 01:04:30,765
Whoa, whoa. Keep your head, mister.

1005
01:04:30,808 --> 01:04:33,143
Else you're liable to lose
it along with your scalp.

1006
01:04:34,603 --> 01:04:36,396
Everything's set.

1007
01:04:36,439 --> 01:04:39,107
I need my volunteers.

1008
01:04:39,150 --> 01:04:40,442
(Woman): Get out there, Phineas.

1009
01:04:40,484 --> 01:04:41,501
- You be a man.
- All right.

1010
01:04:41,531 --> 01:04:44,149
I can give you Clarence
and the other Negroes.

1011
01:04:44,179 --> 01:04:45,258
Best if I stay back

1012
01:04:45,288 --> 01:04:48,685
and watch over the children and womenfolk.

1013
01:04:49,660 --> 01:04:52,370
Bigfoot, let's meander.

1014
01:04:56,379 --> 01:04:58,548
Well, move it.

1015
01:05:43,139 --> 01:05:44,931
(Horse whinnies in the distance)

1016
01:05:50,212 --> 01:05:52,964
Must've hanged your president by now.

1017
01:05:53,007 --> 01:05:54,937
When I know that's true,

1018
01:05:54,967 --> 01:05:56,926
I'll use you for my men's amusement.

1019
01:05:56,969 --> 01:05:59,345
And where will you go?

1020
01:05:59,588 --> 01:06:03,132
Texas... they'll hang you for Goliad.

1021
01:06:03,175 --> 01:06:06,983
In Mexico, they'll shoot
you for San Jacinto.

1022
01:06:07,013 --> 01:06:08,888
- (Smacks)
- (Yelps)

1023
01:06:22,753 --> 01:06:24,854
(Speaks Spanish)

1024
01:06:37,584 --> 01:06:40,628
(Whooping)

1025
01:07:03,784 --> 01:07:07,196
(Whooping)

1026
01:07:25,916 --> 01:07:28,968
(Fuse hissing)

1027
01:07:34,172 --> 01:07:36,184
(Explosion)

1028
01:07:36,226 --> 01:07:39,228
- (Horses neighing)
- (Native Americans whooping)

1029
01:07:42,107 --> 01:07:43,399
Shh.

1030
01:07:43,442 --> 01:07:44,650
(Whooping)

1031
01:07:44,693 --> 01:07:46,069
Now! Fire!

1032
01:07:46,111 --> 01:07:49,113
(Gunshots, whooping, and horses neighing)

1033
01:07:57,206 --> 01:07:59,665
Fire. Fire!

1034
01:07:59,708 --> 01:08:02,710
(Gunshots and whooping)

1035
01:08:22,981 --> 01:08:25,274
Fire, boys. Fire!

1036
01:08:25,317 --> 01:08:28,319
(Whooping)

1037
01:08:31,907 --> 01:08:33,324
(Laughs)

1038
01:08:33,367 --> 01:08:34,951
Come here, boy. We did it!

1039
01:08:34,993 --> 01:08:37,328
- Whoo!
- We drove them off.

1040
01:08:37,371 --> 01:08:40,164
Everybody good over there?

1041
01:08:40,207 --> 01:08:43,459
(All cheering): We done it!

1042
01:08:43,502 --> 01:08:44,669
(Distant cheering)

1043
01:08:44,711 --> 01:08:45,962
I'll be damned.

1044
01:08:46,004 --> 01:08:47,338
It worked!

1045
01:08:47,381 --> 01:08:48,965
Slicker than snot on a doorknob!

1046
01:08:51,176 --> 01:08:53,094
(Woman): Blessed be the saints!

1047
01:08:53,137 --> 01:08:54,929
Saints, hell.

1048
01:08:54,972 --> 01:08:56,848
Thank Jack Hays.

1049
01:08:56,890 --> 01:08:58,141
Come in.

1050
01:08:58,183 --> 01:09:00,059
(Laughter)

1051
01:09:00,102 --> 01:09:01,310
Come in!

1052
01:09:01,353 --> 01:09:04,147
(Laughter)

1053
01:09:04,189 --> 01:09:05,481
Come on in.

1054
01:09:05,524 --> 01:09:07,567
(Laughing)

1055
01:09:18,036 --> 01:09:21,080
- (Flesh sizzling)
- (Groaning)

1056
01:09:24,710 --> 01:09:27,670
(Faint music)

1057
01:09:27,713 --> 01:09:29,313
♪ ♪

1058
01:09:43,602 --> 01:09:45,720
That music,

1059
01:09:46,190 --> 01:09:47,280
is it for me?

1060
01:09:47,310 --> 01:09:48,500
You're famous, Sam.

1061
01:09:48,530 --> 01:09:51,390
Savior of Texas.

1062
01:09:51,420 --> 01:09:52,879
You've got to stay put.

1063
01:09:52,921 --> 01:09:55,298
You're gonna bust open your damn stitches.

1064
01:09:55,341 --> 01:09:57,759
People want to see me.

1065
01:09:57,801 --> 01:09:59,802
Help me.

1066
01:09:59,845 --> 01:10:01,054
Damn it.

1067
01:10:01,096 --> 01:10:03,931
(Houston grunting)

1068
01:10:03,974 --> 01:10:05,641
Put your leg over here.

1069
01:10:05,684 --> 01:10:08,770
(Houston grunting)

1070
01:10:08,812 --> 01:10:10,271
Consarn it, Sam,

1071
01:10:10,314 --> 01:10:12,774
you can't put any weight on that leg.

1072
01:10:12,816 --> 01:10:14,067
That's why I'm leaning on you.

1073
01:10:14,109 --> 01:10:17,111
(Jubilant music and cheering, faintly)

1074
01:10:17,154 --> 01:10:20,740
♪ ♪

1075
01:10:20,783 --> 01:10:22,075
I got him.

1076
01:10:22,117 --> 01:10:25,036
(Jubilant music and cheering)

1077
01:10:25,079 --> 01:10:26,692
♪ ♪

1078
01:10:26,922 --> 01:10:28,381
Thank you.

1079
01:10:28,424 --> 01:10:29,528
(Crowd chanting "Houston!")

1080
01:10:29,558 --> 01:10:31,163
Thank you!

1081
01:10:31,193 --> 01:10:33,285
Give me your hat.

1082
01:10:33,315 --> 01:10:36,322
My hat? Why?

1083
01:10:36,965 --> 01:10:38,132
Thank you!

1084
01:10:38,174 --> 01:10:38,968
(Crowd cheering)

1085
01:10:39,029 --> 01:10:40,368
Sam.

1086
01:10:40,411 --> 01:10:42,996
(Crowd cheering)

1087
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:44,998
Nurse!

1088
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:46,866
That was my best hat.

1089
01:10:46,909 --> 01:10:49,125
♪ ♪

1090
01:10:58,041 --> 01:10:59,429
Be careful.

1091
01:10:59,459 --> 01:11:01,598
(Pauline Wykoff): I need fresh air.

1092
01:11:01,856 --> 01:11:03,767
The wound will reopen.

1093
01:11:03,809 --> 01:11:05,393
(Exhales loudly)

1094
01:11:10,032 --> 01:11:12,859
(Panting)

1095
01:11:19,767 --> 01:11:22,452
What will you do when you're strong again?

1096
01:11:22,495 --> 01:11:25,280
Go back to Tennessee?

1097
01:11:25,310 --> 01:11:27,999
I came out with my husband and kids

1098
01:11:28,042 --> 01:11:29,793
to find a better life.

1099
01:11:33,506 --> 01:11:34,881
I got to stay.

1100
01:11:40,446 --> 01:11:42,310
(Sighs)

1101
01:11:52,912 --> 01:11:55,735
(Men coughing)

1102
01:12:05,332 --> 01:12:09,395
Forbear, Don Antonio. Forbear.

1103
01:12:09,425 --> 01:12:11,811
Portilla will come to save us.

1104
01:12:13,322 --> 01:12:17,474
If I owned both hell and Texas,

1105
01:12:17,934 --> 01:12:21,866
I would rent Texas and live in hell.

1106
01:12:29,253 --> 01:12:30,420
(Girl): Mrs. Smith!

1107
01:12:30,463 --> 01:12:32,589
Mrs. Smith, we got your husband!

1108
01:12:32,631 --> 01:12:34,873
Captain Smith is here.

1109
01:12:37,002 --> 01:12:38,294
Please, give me a hand.

1110
01:12:38,337 --> 01:12:39,567
(Smith): We did it, darling.

1111
01:12:39,597 --> 01:12:41,431
Texas is ours.

1112
01:12:41,474 --> 01:12:43,058
Are you all right?

1113
01:12:49,733 --> 01:12:52,484
Come here.

1114
01:12:52,526 --> 01:12:55,499
Hey, hey, that's him, ain't it?

1115
01:12:55,529 --> 01:12:57,321
- Captain Smith?
- Yes, sir.

1116
01:12:57,364 --> 01:13:00,145
Captain Deaf Smith, fresh from San Jacinto.

1117
01:13:00,175 --> 01:13:01,426
War is won, mostly.

1118
01:13:03,182 --> 01:13:05,054
Splendid.

1119
01:13:05,097 --> 01:13:06,764
We managed to miss it
in search of a trinket.

1120
01:13:06,807 --> 01:13:09,376
Ain't a trinket.

1121
01:13:09,606 --> 01:13:11,619
Hell, if Texas does to us
what it did to him and Samuel,

1122
01:13:11,662 --> 01:13:15,107
we might ought to give California a shot.

1123
01:13:22,631 --> 01:13:25,592
(Faint choral music)

1124
01:13:25,634 --> 01:13:27,234
♪ ♪

1125
01:13:44,723 --> 01:13:47,570
(Baby crying)

1126
01:13:53,937 --> 01:13:55,188
(Doors clatter open)

1127
01:13:55,230 --> 01:13:56,731
(Congregation gasps)

1128
01:13:56,773 --> 01:13:59,775
(All murmuring)

1129
01:14:19,554 --> 01:14:23,933
Christ washed the feet of lepers.

1130
01:14:26,269 --> 01:14:27,490
Thank you for coming.

1131
01:14:27,520 --> 01:14:31,779
This is a special moment
in the life of my grandson.

1132
01:14:36,460 --> 01:14:38,656
(Baby crying)

1133
01:15:06,155 --> 01:15:09,228
(Choir singing softly)

1134
01:15:09,271 --> 01:15:12,857
♪ ♪

1135
01:15:12,899 --> 01:15:14,942
(Doors creak)

1136
01:15:14,972 --> 01:15:20,322
(Doors close heavily)

1137
01:15:20,365 --> 01:15:23,367
(Baby crying)

1138
01:15:40,921 --> 01:15:42,866
Salute, Louis.

1139
01:15:44,890 --> 01:15:47,516
You remember me, mister?

1140
01:15:47,759 --> 01:15:48,968
Yes, ma'am.

1141
01:15:49,010 --> 01:15:52,560
Unfortunate what happened.

1142
01:15:54,099 --> 01:15:56,938
You sold us that place
knowing the Comanches

1143
01:15:56,968 --> 01:15:58,373
were running loose.

1144
01:15:58,403 --> 01:15:59,662
As I recall,

1145
01:15:59,692 --> 01:16:02,494
your husband inquired only
of the Mexican turmoil.

1146
01:16:02,524 --> 01:16:04,404
The subject of Indians never come up.

1147
01:16:04,434 --> 01:16:05,952
(Spits)

1148
01:16:09,119 --> 01:16:11,148
Carts!

1149
01:16:11,191 --> 01:16:12,566
What the hell are you doing out here?

1150
01:16:12,596 --> 01:16:15,424
I told you to get back in there
and finish that goddamn...

1151
01:16:15,454 --> 01:16:17,718
(Shouting indistinctly)

1152
01:16:23,442 --> 01:16:27,173
(Doors creak open)

1153
01:16:28,356 --> 01:16:31,576
(Footsteps)

1154
01:16:58,747 --> 01:17:01,207
(Door creaks open)

1155
01:17:01,249 --> 01:17:02,875
(Door creaks and shuts heavily)

1156
01:17:13,236 --> 01:17:14,870
(Anderson): Colby.

1157
01:17:14,913 --> 01:17:16,514
Hey!

1158
01:17:16,544 --> 01:17:18,641
Round up men for a posse.

1159
01:17:18,684 --> 01:17:20,313
We got a rescue mission.

1160
01:17:20,343 --> 01:17:21,594
Where is Deaf?

1161
01:17:21,636 --> 01:17:22,841
Over there.

1162
01:17:22,871 --> 01:17:24,121
Show the way.

1163
01:17:28,335 --> 01:17:30,085
(Man): Can't go with you. I'm sorry.

1164
01:17:30,128 --> 01:17:32,213
Got my belly full of killing.

1165
01:17:32,490 --> 01:17:34,048
I'll shoe your horses and fix your tack

1166
01:17:34,090 --> 01:17:36,217
free of charge anytime you want.

1167
01:17:36,259 --> 01:17:38,761
(Woman): Erastus is done rangering.

1168
01:17:38,954 --> 01:17:41,163
Let him know peace in his final days.

1169
01:17:41,206 --> 01:17:44,166
Yes, ma'am. Yes, ma'am.

1170
01:17:44,209 --> 01:17:47,503
We're just here to look after
his well-being

1171
01:17:47,545 --> 01:17:48,921
and to pay our respects.

1172
01:17:48,964 --> 01:17:50,172
You think I don't see?

1173
01:17:50,215 --> 01:17:52,091
There is trouble somewhere.

1174
01:17:52,133 --> 01:17:53,425
You want men.

1175
01:17:54,761 --> 01:17:58,347
There's been a kidnapping.

1176
01:17:58,390 --> 01:18:00,724
Yeah, the lady who
helped us beat Santa Anna.

1177
01:18:00,767 --> 01:18:02,977
You found Emily West?

1178
01:18:03,019 --> 01:18:05,020
You get back in that bed.

1179
01:18:05,063 --> 01:18:06,563
I've got to take a country leak, woman,

1180
01:18:06,606 --> 01:18:08,691
unless you want to mop up this floor.

1181
01:18:08,733 --> 01:18:09,984
Bueno.

1182
01:18:16,527 --> 01:18:19,118
Deaf. This is...

1183
01:18:19,148 --> 01:18:21,233
Captain Smith, name's Jack Hays.

1184
01:18:21,263 --> 01:18:22,367
This here is Bigfoot Wallace.

1185
01:18:22,397 --> 01:18:24,273
It's a real honor to meet you, sir. I...

1186
01:18:24,316 --> 01:18:26,233
Are you the Tennessee
turned up and saved this town

1187
01:18:26,276 --> 01:18:27,687
from the Comanches?

1188
01:18:27,717 --> 01:18:29,039
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

1189
01:18:30,739 --> 01:18:32,365
That was nice work.

1190
01:18:32,407 --> 01:18:34,504
Thank you.

1191
01:18:35,125 --> 01:18:36,837
Hey, come on.

1192
01:18:38,090 --> 01:18:41,061
Deaf, we're... we're not here
to give you any trouble.

1193
01:18:41,091 --> 01:18:43,967
We... we don't want
to cause a commotion.

1194
01:18:43,997 --> 01:18:45,177
We just don't want to...

1195
01:18:45,220 --> 01:18:46,824
Though we could use your advice.

1196
01:18:46,854 --> 01:18:47,980
Please.

1197
01:18:48,352 --> 01:18:50,107
Advice.

1198
01:18:52,546 --> 01:18:54,611
Don't marry a woman that can whoop you.

1199
01:18:54,654 --> 01:18:57,656
She'll make you piss yourself.

1200
01:18:57,699 --> 01:18:59,365
Portilla's got her. Don't he?

1201
01:18:59,395 --> 01:19:00,826
That's right.

1202
01:19:00,868 --> 01:19:03,144
I think I remember seeing him ride off.

1203
01:19:03,174 --> 01:19:06,044
I figured she was dead.

1204
01:19:06,074 --> 01:19:07,783
Didn't tell nobody.

1205
01:19:07,813 --> 01:19:10,786
(Coughing)

1206
01:19:23,692 --> 01:19:25,777
I'm gonna need a new mount.

1207
01:19:26,844 --> 01:19:28,771
(Anderson): Done.

1208
01:19:28,813 --> 01:19:30,631
(Woman): Excuse me.

1209
01:19:35,658 --> 01:19:37,362
Deaf, no.

1210
01:19:37,405 --> 01:19:39,794
If you go out that door,

1211
01:19:39,824 --> 01:19:42,021
we know you ain't coming back.

1212
01:19:42,051 --> 01:19:45,618
Lupe, darling,

1213
01:19:46,058 --> 01:19:49,420
I am coughing blood and farting dust.

1214
01:19:51,377 --> 01:19:53,087
Now, I reckon I can die in that bed

1215
01:19:53,129 --> 01:19:56,006
watching all your caterwauling,

1216
01:19:56,049 --> 01:19:58,133
or I can die as I've tried my damnedest

1217
01:19:58,176 --> 01:20:00,648
to live all my days:

1218
01:20:00,678 --> 01:20:02,592
Like a man.

1219
01:20:06,851 --> 01:20:10,540
You done real good keeping
me around this long.

1220
01:20:11,176 --> 01:20:14,079
Can you do one more thing?

1221
01:20:14,109 --> 01:20:17,281
You mind fetching me my clothes?

1222
01:20:32,854 --> 01:20:35,040
Those look real good.

1223
01:20:37,885 --> 01:20:40,438
Mind your chores,

1224
01:20:40,676 --> 01:20:43,744
and you be a comfort to your ma, you hear?

1225
01:20:44,180 --> 01:20:46,682
Now, when you get older, well,

1226
01:20:47,049 --> 01:20:51,103
I'm gonna expect you
to account for yourself.

1227
01:20:51,270 --> 01:20:54,981
Texas is gonna need a
young lady like yourself.

1228
01:20:55,611 --> 01:20:57,781
All right?

1229
01:20:59,333 --> 01:21:02,214
I'm mighty proud of you.

1230
01:21:14,377 --> 01:21:17,504
There ain't words for how much I love you.

1231
01:21:33,479 --> 01:21:35,339
(Anderson): Make way!

1232
01:21:50,079 --> 01:21:51,288
(Knock at door)

1233
01:21:51,331 --> 01:21:52,915
(Man): Sam.

1234
01:21:52,957 --> 01:21:55,792
Your enemies are conspiring
against you as we speak.

1235
01:21:55,835 --> 01:22:00,547
(Burnet): He and Houston
want to annex our Texas.

1236
01:22:02,634 --> 01:22:06,929
If you would accept this...

1237
01:22:06,971 --> 01:22:09,014
It must be used for good.

1238
01:22:09,057 --> 01:22:11,266
Your land is now forfiet
as well as the collateral...

1239
01:22:11,309 --> 01:22:13,019
You can't have Nate.

1240
01:22:14,646 --> 01:22:16,772
What about this one?

1241
01:22:16,814 --> 01:22:19,149
Shoo, shoo, in the kitchen.

1242
01:22:19,192 --> 01:22:22,861
Santa Anna's whore doesn't
eat with decent folk.

1243
01:22:22,904 --> 01:22:25,781
I very much like your house.

1244
01:22:25,823 --> 01:22:27,159
It would suit me.

1245
01:22:27,189 --> 01:22:29,047
They may have cleaned you up.

1246
01:22:29,077 --> 01:22:30,665
I know you.

1247
01:22:30,695 --> 01:22:34,156
What do we got to do to join
up with a ranger company?

1248
01:22:34,199 --> 01:22:37,826
(Gunshots)

1249
01:22:37,869 --> 01:22:39,536
(Whooping)

1250
01:22:39,579 --> 01:22:41,747
(Shouts)

1251
01:22:41,790 --> 01:22:44,145
And I suggest you finish
up your little party here

1252
01:22:44,175 --> 01:22:45,634
and come with us and get back home

1253
01:22:45,677 --> 01:22:47,565
and fix Texas before it's too late.

1254
01:22:48,319 --> 01:22:55,709
